31/05/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu signed a decree Monday (30 May) establishing an organised crime and terrorism investigation department within the public order ministry. 
Basescu's office says two British advisers to the president -- specialising in anti-corruption activities and EU accession issues -- officially assumed their duties Monday. 
The British government is financing the yearlong project, aimed at facilitating Romania's entry into the EU. 
Two more special presidential advisers are expected in Bucharest soon. 
(Rompres, Ziarul financiar - 31/05/05)
